================================================================================
License compatibility notes
================================================================================

`doc-rag` is licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later, which is compatible with
all of the runtime dependencies and most optional extras listed above.

The default `pip install -e .` (with no extras) pulls only MIT, BSD,
MPL-2.0, and Apache-2.0 code, which would also be compatible with a more
permissive project license, should you fork doc-rag under different
terms — at which point you must keep the original AGPL notice for the
portions you re-use, per the AGPL itself.

The `[pdf]` and `[ocr]` extras include PyMuPDF, which is **AGPL-3.0**.
This is intentional and matches doc-rag's own license; no additional
constraints are introduced over what AGPL-3.0 already requires.
